post_summaries.description: The image is a text-based meme posted by vegansmusing on Instagram. The word "Vegan" is written in large, green cursive font at the top. Below, in smaller, black block letters, the text reads: "A PERSON WHO HAS THE CRAZY IDEA THAT ANIMALS SHOULDN'T SUFFER." The post includes the hashtags #vegan #veganmeme #veganism #veganfollowback #veganforlife #veganaf.
The image is a close-up shot of a vegan Buffalo Ranch "Chick'n" sandwich made with oyster mushrooms. It looks delicious and is posted by the account @vegansmusing.

The image is a meme about vegan food. It shows a bowl of healthy vegan food (grains, vegetables) above the text "Vegan Food: When it's good - it's really, really good." Below that is the text "And when it's bad - well... it's still not a DEAD ANIMAL!" with a cartoon image of french fries.
The image shows a colorful vegan sushi platter from a restaurant called "Garden of Eden" in Windsor. The platter includes various types of vegan sushi, fried items, and dipping sauces.

The image is of a box of M&S Bran Flakes cereal. The post is by an account called "vegansmusing" and the caption praises the cereal as a good vegan option. The caption also mentions eating the cereal in the sun to get vitamin D.
The image shows a vegan sandwich made with tofu scramble, vegan mayo, and tortilla chips on a bun. It's placed on a green plate with some extra tortilla chips on the side.
